Identification_notes: (Forsskal) Borgesen, 1932; combined Dictyosphaeria cavernosa and versluysii; full morphology lit link: https://www.hawaii.edu/reefalgae/invasive_algae/chloro/dictyosphaeria_versluysii.htm
Dana, 1846; max size based on G. pectinata and G. palauensis
(Hudson) Papenfuss, 1950; now Gracilariopsis longissima (S.G.Gmelin) Steentoft, L.M.Irvine & Famham, 1995
UC Berkeley Moorea Biocode Project records (Pauley et al. 2009); called Grey Sponge in notes and survey datasets
Quoy and Gaimard, 1833; previously Heteractis magnifica; hundreds of years life span
de Laubenfels, 1954; Freeman and Easson 2016; authors indicate may be phototrophic
Glynn, Mate & Stemann, 2001; size based on P varians and P cf explanulata
Lamarck, 1816; growth based on p. damicornis
Quelch, 1884; endemic to Polynesia and different from Verrill, 1864 which is a synonym of Porites rus
